==English==
===Etymology===
From the Spanish [[juzgado]] (pronounced /xuθ'gað̞o/ in careful speech, but /xuθ'gao/ in relaxed or rapid speech for some regions; the /θ/ is realized as [s] in Latin America and southern Spain), meaning [[court]], [[courthouse]].

===Noun===
'''hoosegow''' (uncountable)
#{{slang}} [[jail]]
#:''He was so drunk they took him to the '''hoosegow''' to dry out.

